    explanation: 'Though private pilots typically operate below 18,000 ft, the written exam tests knowledge of high-altitude concepts including Class A airspace, oxygen requirements, and pressurization principles. Above FL180 (18,000 ft MSL), all operations are IFR in Class A airspace. Pressure at altitude is insufficient to maintain consciousness — hence supplemental oxygen requirements. Turbocharged engines maintain sea-level power to their critical altitude by compressing inlet air.',
